\is1 Introduction
\ip At the time when the preaching of the good message about Jesus began to spread and it started being accepted by non-Jews, an important question arose: whether or not it's necessary for a person wanting to accept the message to also obey the Law of Moses. Paul argues that it's not necessary because it's by faith that we can receive life from the messiah, pinaahi rue to become correct there in front of God the person. But there to me group of believers of Galasya, the one province of Ruma there to Asia Minur, due people migsupak ki Paul and believed the person it's necessary obey iya of Law of Moses so that to become correct there in front of God.
\ip In \bk Paul's letter to the assemblies in Galatia\bk*, he wrote so that egpakalibed there to true/correct faith that people neuyan of not true/correct teaching. Imbunsuran din this by means of telling din ke what the reason neyimu sikandin apostle. Migpamalehet sikandin not there from power of people the pegkaapustulis din because there iya of God and labew of all, there sikandin ipeuyan of God of non-Jews. Ne dutu, strove sikandin the egpakig-apul ware lein paahi to become correct there in front of God the people, gawas of faith just iya.
\ip There in ending me kapitulu, answered din that migkahi of bad kun ke not obey of Law the one person. Said si Paul of makaaldek-haldek ke eg-engked sikandan of goodness and mercy of God egpeuripen of Law of Moses. Migtambahan din again sikandan of it's necessary egpasakup sikandan of Spirit of God so that egkabalbalawan sikandan and kenad egpekeikul of igkeupii of body ran makasesale.
